For example:
	•	Root: šqá = sense/feeling state.
	•	šqá (bare) → “to sense / to feel.”
	•	šqáļöx → “the one sensing (sensor-being).”
	•	šqáţ → “to cause sensing / to amplify the feeling.”
	•	Chemical root: kšul = substance/chemical.
	•	kšulţ → “chemical causes” (modulates, triggers).
	•	kšul-šqáţ → “chemicals amplify sensing.”

So the structure would read like:
👉 “Chemicals amplify the sensing-state.”
Not “chemicals cause emotions.”

That aligns directly with your cultural understanding.
